verbose_text: Secondary causes for reversible cerebral vasoconstriction syndrome (RCVS) like subarachnoid hemorrhage (SAH) were ruled out from negative computed tomography head (CT) and lumbar puncture (LP), while vasculitis was excluded from the laboratory findings that showed normal erythrocyte sedimentation rate (ESR), anti-nuclear antibody (ANA), anti-neutrophil cytoplasmic antibody (ANCA) P & C, cryoglobulin, complement, rheumatoid factor (RF), anti SS-A and SS-B levels along with unremarkable cerebrospinal fluid analysis (CSF).
